thread.title: New York High Schools See Increase in College Admission Test Takers

author: Leslie Brody
title: New York High Schools See Increase in College Admission Test Takers

organizations.name: new york high schools see increase

text:
A record-high number of juniors in New York City’s public high schools during the last academic year took the SAT exam for college admission, thanks to the city’s offer of free testing for 11th graders last spring, city officials said Thursday.
The city’s Department of Education said 61,800 juniors last year took the SAT, up 51% from the previous year. Officials said the gap in participation rates narrowed among different groups.
